The paper deals with connectivity in graphs, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of short cycles as a means of connectivity is a novel approach, and is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), social networks (cs.SI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
